{"id":"fe63a758-c98a-4dc9-adb9-de006739d30e","object":"chat.completion","created":1769111396,"model":"deepseek-reasoner","choices":[{"index":0,"message":{"role":"assistant","content":"The factorial of 5, denoted as 5!, is calculated as follows:\n\n\\[\n5! = 5 \\times 4 \\times 3 \\times 2 \\times 1\n\\]\n\nStep-by-step multiplication:\n- \\( 5 \\times 4 = 20 \\)\n- \\( 20 \\times 3 = 60 \\)\n- \\( 60 \\times 2 = 120 \\)\n- \\( 120 \\times 1 = 120 \\)\n\nThus, \\( 5! = 120 \\).","reasoning_content":"We are asked: \"What is the factorial of 5? Show your work. Think before you answer.\" This is straightforward. The factorial of 5, denoted as 5!, is the product of all positive integers from 1 to 5. So, 5! = 5 × 4 × 3 × 2 × 1. We can compute step by step.\n\nLet's compute:\n5 × 4 = 20\n20 × 3 = 60\n60 × 2 = 120\n120 × 1 = 120\n\nSo, 5! = 120.\n\nWe should show our work as requested. The answer is 120."},"logprobs":null,"finish_reason":"stop"}],"usage":{"prompt_tokens":21,"completion_tokens":248,"total_tokens":269,"prompt_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":0},"completion_tokens_details":{"reasoning_tokens":138},"prompt_cache_hit_tokens":0,"prompt_cache_miss_tokens":21},"system_fingerprint":"fp_eaab8d114b_prod0820_fp8_kvcache"}